cientists, urban developers, and policy makers. Synthesizing insights from ecology, environmental history, public policy analysis, and urban planning as she tracks these debates over the course of the past twenty-five years, Audrey L. Mayer presents an ultimately optimistic take on the importance of much-neglected regional conservation planning strategies to create sustainable urban landscapes that benefit humans and wildlife alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aCalifornia gnatcatcherxHabitatxConservationzCalifornia. 0aCoastal ecologyzCalifornia. 0aHabitat conservationzCalifornia, SouthernxHistory. 0aHabitat conservationzCalifornia. 0aNature conservationzCalifornia, SouthernxHistory. 0aNature conservationzCalifornia. 7aNATURE / Animals / Birds.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075414808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021z9783110753912oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300258608423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300258608.jpg  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075414-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DPMb2021